   <td colspan="4" class="content">
    <pre>Awesome, I have tested this in Firebug and it looks great!

The next step would be to get it into the OpenHatch source. We store most of our
CSS files (not the wiki's one so far) in the main repository for
version-tracking purposes. So the best way to go forward would be for you to
clone a local copy of the OpenHatch source, make your change there and then
submit a patch using "git format-patch".

The CSS files are kept in mysite/static/css. You can find steps on how to get an
OpenHatch clone set up at
<a href="https://openhatch.org/wiki/Getting_started_with_the_OpenHatch_code">https://openhatch.org/wiki/Getting_started_with_the_OpenHatch_code</a> and if you
have any questions or problems, feel free to ask here or on IRC.

Also, it's great to have another new patch contributor =)</pre>
